WEBVTT

00:04.838 --> 00:05.806 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Good evening.

00:05.839 --> 00:07.307 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm Judy Woodruff.

00:07.341 --> 00:10.978 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
On the "NewsHour" tonight: The
nation reacts
to a new president-elect.

00:11.011 --> 00:17.384 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We hear from voices across
generations and
zip codes on the future of the
free world.

00:17.417 --> 00:19.253 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
And it's Friday.

00:19.286 --> 00:23.924 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Mark Shields and David Brooks
give their take
on a momentous week, the start
of a new chapter

00:23.957 --> 00:25.959 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
in American political life.

00:25.993 --> 00:32.766 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Plus: Paris one year later -- as
the Bataclan
club reopens for the first time
since the

00:32.799 --> 00:35.802 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
terrorism attacks, a look at how
the city
is coping.

00:35.836 --> 00:38.472 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CAROLINE LANGLADE, President,
Life for Paris
(through translator): I think
that the most

00:38.505 --> 00:43.744 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
beautiful response we can give
the terrorists
is love, joy, happiness,
culture, music.

00:43.777 --> 00:46.780 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, we need to keep this going
as loud as
possible.

00:46.813 --> 00:55.522 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: All that and more
on tonight's
"PBS NewsHour."

00:55.555 --> 00:58.492 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

00:58.525 --> 01:07.334 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: President-elect
Donald Trump
announced a shakeup today at the
top of his

01:07.367 --> 01:09.703 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
incoming transition team.

01:09.736 --> 01:14.975 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Vice president-elect Mike Pence
will take
over as chair, replacing New
Jersey Governor

01:15.008 --> 01:18.278 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Chris Christie, who becomes a
vice chair.

01:18.312 --> 01:22.749 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Former House Speaker Newt
Gingrich and former
New York City Mayor Rudy
Giuliani will be

01:22.783 --> 01:26.653 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
among the other vice chairs on
the executive
committee.

01:26.687 --> 01:31.892 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Members of the committee also
include Mr.
Trump's three older children
Donald Jr., Eric

01:31.925 --> 01:36.897 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and Ivanka, as well as Ivanka's
husband, son-in-law
Jared Kushner.

01:36.930 --> 01:41.835 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
In a statement, the
president-elect said -- quote
-- "Together, we will begin the
urgent task

01:41.868 --> 01:47.341 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of rebuilding this nation,
specifically jobs,
security and opportunity."

01:47.374 --> 01:51.778 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And in his first news interview
since the
election, Mr. Trump told The
Wall Street Journal

01:51.812 --> 01:56.249 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
he is open to keeping some parts
of the Affordable
Care Act.

01:56.283 --> 02:01.588 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We will have more on Mr. Trump's
post-election
moves later in the program.

02:01.621 --> 02:06.393 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Protesters nationwide spent
another night
rallying against the
president-elect.

02:06.426 --> 02:11.698 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Demonstrations came to a head in
Portland,
Oregon, where thousands squared
off with police,

02:11.732 --> 02:13.967 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
throwing bottles and rocks.

02:14.001 --> 02:16.670 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Officers responded with tear gas
and rubber
bullets.

02:16.703 --> 02:18.939 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
They made 26 arrests.

02:18.972 --> 02:24.144 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
For his part, Mr. Trump tweeted
that the protesters
were -- quote -- "very unfair,"
but later

02:24.177 --> 02:27.781 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
said he "loved their passion for
our great
country."

02:27.814 --> 02:33.387 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The United Nations says the
Islamic State
has carried out a new wave of
public killings

02:33.420 --> 02:36.723 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and atrocities in the Iraqi city
of Mosul.

02:36.757 --> 02:42.062 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It reports that, in the last
week, militants
executed at least 70 civilians.

02:42.095 --> 02:44.297 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Some were hung from telephone
poles.

02:44.331 --> 02:49.436 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Meanwhile, in Geneva, a
spokeswoman for the
U.N. said the group could be
gearing up to

02:49.469 --> 02:51.271 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
use chemical weapons.

02:51.304 --> 02:53.206 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RAVINA SHAMSADANI, Spokeswoman,
United Nations
High Commissioner for Human
Rights: We don't

02:53.240 --> 02:57.711 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
know when and for what purposes
they are stockpiling
these, but given what they have
done in the

02:57.744 --> 03:03.483 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
past, we are worried about the
reasons for
their stockpiling of these
chemicals in Mosul

03:03.517 --> 03:04.851 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
right now.

03:04.885 --> 03:08.321 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But we can only speculate how
they -- they
intend to use this.

03:08.355 --> 03:13.860 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The announcement
comes as Iraqi
security forces inched their way
into Mosul.

03:13.894 --> 03:19.166 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They have been slowed by heavy
resistance
and ISIS fighters using human
shields.

03:19.199 --> 03:24.538 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Back in this country, President
Obama used
Veterans Day to call for unity
in the wake

03:24.571 --> 03:26.306 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of a bitter election.

03:26.339 --> 03:31.411 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Mr. Obama laid a wreath at The
Tomb of the
Unknown at Arlington National
Cemetery.

03:31.445 --> 03:36.149 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He said Americans should learn
from the military
in finding ways to come
together.

03:36.183 --> 03:39.319 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BARACK OBAMA, President of the
United States:
The American instinct has never
been to find

03:39.352 --> 03:41.521 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
isolation in opposite corners.

03:41.555 --> 03:49.729 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It is to find strength in our
common creed,
to forge unity from our great
diversity, to

03:49.763 --> 03:53.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
sustain that strength and unity
even when
it is hard.

03:53.433 --> 03:58.238 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Meanwhile,
Britain and France
commemorated Armistice Day,
marking the end

03:58.271 --> 04:04.177 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of World War I. Prince Harry led
a service
at the Armed Forces Memorial in
England, while

04:04.211 --> 04:10.617 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
French President Francois
Hollande laid a
wreath at his country's Tomb of
the Unknown.

04:10.650 --> 04:14.921 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Stocks were mixed on Wall Street
today, but
the Dow Jones industrial average
closed at

04:14.955 --> 04:19.860 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a record high, extending its
post-election
rally for another day.

04:19.893 --> 04:24.531 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Dow gained more than 39
points to close
at 18847.

04:24.564 --> 04:30.003 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Nasdaq rose 28, while the
S&amp;P 500 slipped
three.

04:30.036 --> 04:35.275 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
For the week, the Dow gained
more than 5 percent,
its best week since December
2011.

04:35.308 --> 04:40.814 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Both the Nasdaq and the S&amp;P 500
rose nearly
4 percent.

04:40.847 --> 04:45.952 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And Secretary of State John
Kerry has become
the highest ranking U.S.
official to visit

04:45.986 --> 04:47.721 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Antarctica.

04:47.754 --> 04:51.525 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He's spending two days there,
meeting with
scientists and getting a
firsthand look at

04:51.558 --> 04:55.529 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the impact that climate change
has had on
the southernmost continent.

04:55.562 --> 05:01.768 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Kerry is gathering information
before he attends
a global climate change summit
in Morocco

05:01.801 --> 05:03.537 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
on Tuesday.

05:03.570 --> 05:08.141 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Still to come on the "NewsHour":
the fallout
from a sharply divided election
plays out

05:08.175 --> 05:13.547 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in schools across the nation;
Mark Shields
and David Brooks on what voters
were saying

05:13.580 --> 05:20.053 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and what lies ahead; healing in
Paris one
year after deadly terror attacks
darkened

05:20.086 --> 05:33.366 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the City of Light; and much
more.

05:33.400 --> 05:36.369 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Now more on the aftermath of
Tuesday's election.

05:36.403 --> 05:41.541 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We take two looks at the ways
that the rhetoric
and emotion of the highly
charged presidential

05:41.575 --> 05:43.743 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
campaign continue to
reverberate.

05:43.777 --> 05:49.649 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
First, we go to Manassas,
Virginia, about
30 miles West of Washington,
D.C., near the

05:49.683 --> 05:52.852 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
site of the first major battle
of the Civil
War.

05:52.886 --> 05:58.425 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
After decades of supporting
Republicans, Virginia
voted Democratic on Tuesday for
the third

05:58.458 --> 06:00.527 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
consecutive presidential
election.

06:00.560 --> 06:07.167 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The state's demographics are
shifting rapidly,
and like much of America, the
division between

06:07.200 --> 06:09.402 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
red and blue is stark.

06:09.436 --> 06:13.640 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We spoke with people from across
of the political
spectrum caught up in the wake
of one of the

06:13.673 --> 06:17.344 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
biggest political upsets in our
nation's history.

06:17.377 --> 06:19.112 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Here are some of their voices.

06:19.145 --> 06:23.216 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BRETT TUCKER, Trump Voter: A lot
of division
has occurred in this great
country over the

06:23.250 --> 06:32.726 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
last decade, and a lot of them
is almost reflective
to the time period of when the
guns blazed

06:32.759 --> 06:34.694 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
on this battlefield and men
fought for what
they believed in.

06:34.728 --> 06:40.166 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think America is kind of
in the same
scenario where we're divided on
our beliefs

06:40.200 --> 06:41.901 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in politics.

06:41.935 --> 06:46.539 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
To me, as I travel the country,
I just feel
the sense of urgency to repair
it.

06:46.573 --> 06:49.476 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I'm Brett Tucker, 46, from
Washington state.

06:49.509 --> 06:50.910 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And I voted for Mr. Trump.

06:50.944 --> 06:54.481 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
DON CLEMONS, Trump Voter: My
name is Don Clemons.

06:54.514 --> 06:56.149 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I am 80 years old.

06:56.182 --> 07:01.288 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I live at St. Joseph, Illinois,
and I voted
for Donald Trump for president.

07:01.321 --> 07:06.693 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I have seen John Kennedy, and I
didn't vote
for him.

07:06.726 --> 07:08.261 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I wished I would have.

07:08.295 --> 07:13.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I have seen Ronald Reagan,
Dwight Eisenhower,
you know, during my lifetime.

07:13.600 --> 07:18.905 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
See, I have voted in every
presidential election
since 1958.

07:18.938 --> 07:20.707 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I think that's about right.

07:20.740 --> 07:26.379 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And these are the two weakest
candidates that
I have ever seen that I had to
vote for.

07:26.413 --> 07:27.380 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
SUSAN ARTZ, Trump Voter: I'm
Susan Artz.

07:27.414 --> 07:28.381 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I'm from Aldie, Virginia.

07:28.415 --> 07:29.883 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm 67 years old.

07:29.916 --> 07:33.620 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I voted for Donald Trump for
president
of the United States of America.

07:33.653 --> 07:37.190 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think these other countries
should do more
of their share.

07:37.223 --> 07:43.963 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They pay so much less for NATO
than we do.

07:43.997 --> 07:46.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I traveled around the world by
the time I
was 21.

07:46.866 --> 07:50.670 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I looked at all they have,
like he says,
with our infrastructure, with
the railroads

07:50.704 --> 07:56.242 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and all, and they have so much
better than
we do.

07:56.276 --> 07:58.211 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
VANESSA ALLEN, Trump Voter: I'm
Vanessa Allen.

07:58.244 --> 08:02.349 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I'm retired, and life is not
easy, and I am
a Democrat.

08:02.382 --> 08:04.684 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I think we have got a lot of
dummies.

08:04.718 --> 08:06.519 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
I really do.

08:06.553 --> 08:12.959 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I mean, if you truly listen to
what he says,
I don't even see how you can
push that button

08:12.992 --> 08:15.729 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
on that computer voting for him.

08:15.762 --> 08:18.031 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It's just -- it's crazy.

08:18.064 --> 08:23.670 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I worked all my life, never
took, never got,
unless I made it.

08:23.703 --> 08:28.575 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And now what, you know?

08:28.608 --> 08:32.679 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, I don't think he will do
anything great.

08:32.712 --> 08:33.847 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
I really don't.

08:33.880 --> 08:36.015 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SALIM AMIN, Sanders Voter: My
name is Salim
Amin.

08:36.049 --> 08:39.152 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I'm 23 years old, and I voted
Bernie Sanders
as a write-in.

08:39.185 --> 08:40.720 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I was born in Germany.

08:40.754 --> 08:42.956 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And my parents are from
Afghanistan.

08:42.989 --> 08:45.525 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I'm not primarily concerned
about the president
himself.

08:45.558 --> 08:51.398 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I'm more concerned about the
people he's riled
up, the actual racist people,
the misogynistic

08:51.431 --> 08:57.303 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
people that are feeling like
they were -- fueled
the fire to be able to make sure
-- whatever

08:57.337 --> 08:59.072 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
they want to do.

08:59.105 --> 09:03.343 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LAMYAA MOWERY, Virginia: We
can't succumb
to what they want, and we need
to be much

09:03.376 --> 09:09.449 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
stronger than we ever were
before.

09:09.482 --> 09:13.953 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NATHAN MOWERY, Virginia: I'm
Nathan Mowery,
and I'm a five-year Army combat
veteran.

09:13.987 --> 09:14.954 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
This is my wife.

09:14.988 --> 09:16.489 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
LAMYAA MOWERY: And I'm Lamyaa
Mowery.

09:16.523 --> 09:17.957 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm a nursing student.

09:17.991 --> 09:21.561 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
NATHAN MOWERY: And we just got
married in
October.

09:21.594 --> 09:23.730 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And we are here in our house in
Virginia.

09:23.763 --> 09:30.370 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LAMYAA MOWERY: Already, after we
found out
that president-elect Trump won,
people have

09:30.403 --> 09:32.238 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
gotten bolder.

09:32.272 --> 09:38.745 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There have been cases where
women are pumping
gas and they have been yelled at
to take off

09:38.778 --> 09:42.982 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
their scarf, or walking in a
grocery store
and telling them that this is
going to be

09:43.016 --> 09:46.352 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the end of you and it's time for
you to leave.

09:46.386 --> 09:50.757 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And it's only the beginning, and
I'm sure
that everyone is going to see a
rise in it.

09:50.790 --> 09:52.759 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ALICE BUTLER-SHORT, Founder and
Director,
Virginia Women for Trump: When
Mr. Trump says

09:52.792 --> 09:58.431 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
make America great again, he
means let's bring
it back to where it was and move
forward and

09:58.465 --> 10:00.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
make it even greater.

10:00.467 --> 10:03.903 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I am absolutely convinced
that he will
do that.

10:03.937 --> 10:05.772 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
My name is Alice Butler-Short.

10:05.805 --> 10:09.576 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I am the founder and director
for Virginia
Women for Trump.

10:09.609 --> 10:14.113 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Immigrants will always be
welcome in this
country, but the right
immigrants.

10:14.147 --> 10:21.354 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We have got to keep this country
safe, and
we have had experiences of
terrorism and terrorist

10:21.387 --> 10:22.355 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
attacks.

10:22.388 --> 10:23.957 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And we know it's not going to
end.

10:23.990 --> 10:25.458 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
So, we have to take precautions.

10:25.492 --> 10:30.029 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
THOMAS VLADIMIR MENDOZA, Opposed
Trump: My
name is Thomas Vladimir Mendoza.

10:30.063 --> 10:31.231 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And I am a U.S. citizen.

10:31.264 --> 10:33.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I live in the United States, so
I'm American.

10:33.967 --> 10:36.636 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
But I was born in El Salvador.

10:36.669 --> 10:43.243 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
