day -- in the
next election, we can make sure
that we make

13:03.650 --> 13:06.753 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
our voices heard, that we are
the ones running
for Senate, we are the ones
running for president,

13:06.786 --> 13:09.389 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
we are the ones representing us
in the communities.

13:09.422 --> 13:13.026 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
TIMMY JOSTEN, Student: My
concerns are that
Donald is kind of going to lose
his temper

13:13.059 --> 13:18.398 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a little bit sometimes and say
some not-so-smart
things and get some people
angry.

13:18.431 --> 13:21.267 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But I don't think he's going to
make too many
bad decisions.

13:21.301 --> 13:22.435 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I think he knows where he's
going.

13:22.468 --> 13:24.237 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I think he knows what he's
doing.

13:24.270 --> 13:27.206 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARY OLIVER, Student: The fact
that someone
like Trump is able to be
elected, the things

13:27.240 --> 13:31.411 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that he says for women, about
people in different
races, the fact that it's OK for
him to say

13:31.444 --> 13:35.014 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
those things now makes it seem
