38:51.629 --> 38:56.267 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
worst attack on the French
capital since the
Second World War, nothing will
ever be the

38:56.301 --> 38:58.069 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
same again.

38:58.102 --> 39:03.308 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In a discreet corner of this
cafe is Caroline
Langlade, a survivor of the
Bataclan.

39:03.341 --> 39:08.313 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Along with several others, she
hid in a tiny
room for over three hours.

39:08.346 --> 39:11.916 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They barricaded the door with a
sofa and mini-fridge.

39:11.950 --> 39:16.888 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The terrorists tried to get in,
failed and
resumed the massacre they began
while the

39:16.921 --> 39:18.756 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
band was on stage.

39:18.790 --> 39:20.592 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(GUNFIRE)

39:20.625 --> 39:26.764 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CAROLINE LANGLADE, President,
Life for Paris
(through translator): I have a
really hard

39:26.798 --> 39:31.936 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
time going to closed-up places
or dark rooms,
movies, concerts, but also
restaurants where

39:31.970 --> 39:32.971 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
there's too many people at
night.

39:33.004 --> 39:35.406 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It makes me quite jumpy.

39:35.440 --> 39:37.842 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
I tend to panic.

39:37.875 --> 39:44.949 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: During the
interview, sirens
wailed nearby, and Caroline
became uncomfortable.

39:44.983 --> 39:49.087 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The film director has found it
difficult to
concentrate on work and instead
devotes her

39:49.120 --> 39:54.626 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
energies running Life for Paris,
an organization
for survivors and families of
those murdered

39:54.659 --> 39:56.060 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
on Friday the 13th.

39:56.094 --> 40:00.265 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CAROLINE LANGLADE (through
translator): I'm
no longer afraid of death.

40:00.298 --> 40:04.302 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I have seen it up close, and I
almost died
several times that night.

40:04.335 --> 40:07.438 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I'm no longer afraid of death,
but my fear
changed.

40:07.472 --> 40:13.378 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, today, what frightens me
most is suffering,
physical suffering, human
suffering.

40:13.411 --> 40:17.882 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I had to face a gigantic amount
of it that
evening, and I think that I have
lived through

40:17.915 --> 40:20.585 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
all the suffering I could have
had for a lifetime.

40:20.618 --> 40:25.657 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: This video
captured the panic
and bravery of survivors as they
fled the

40:25.690 --> 40:30.094 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Bataclan and tried to drag the
wounded and
dying to safety.

40:30.128 --> 40:34.299 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Parents watching the atrocities
unfold on
television desperately hoped
their children

40:34.332 --> 40:37.001 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
had made it through the
emergency exits.

40:37.035 --> 40:44.142 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
For Georges Salines, the
anniversary rekindles
the agony of discovering that
his music-loving

40:44.175 --> 40:46.678 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
daughter, Lola, was one of the
89 murder victims.

40:46.711 --> 40:50.748 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
®MD-BO /GEORGES SALINES, Father
of Victim:
What I miss the most is simply
talking to

40:50.782 --> 40:59.724 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
her and listening to her about
her new discoveries,
because she was always full of
projects.

40:59.757 --> 41:02.660 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
For me, the most important thing
was writing.

41:02.694 --> 41:04.862 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
I wrote a book.

41:04.896 --> 41:09.067 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And after publishing my book, I
kept on writing.

41:09.100 --> 41:15.039 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And writing has been very
helpful, because
it helps me to put some distance
between my

41:15.073 --> 41:16.841 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
pain and me.

41:16.874 --> 41:22.146 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: After a year of
silence,
the Bataclan is about to be
revived as a concert

41:22.180 --> 41:27.985 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
hall for the living, no longer
just a shrine
to contemplate the unspeakable.

41:28.019 --> 41:32.290 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
One year after Friday the 13th,
France remains
under a state of emergency.

41:32.323 --> 41:38.363 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The powers were expanded and
extended after
the horrific attack in Nice,
when a terrorist

41:38.396 --> 41:43.935 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
took a truck and mowed down
people, killing
86 and wounding nearly 500.

41:43.968 --> 41:48.973 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
France's interior minister says
the country
cannot live in an indefinite
state of emergency.

41:49.006 --> 41:54.312 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And groups like Human Rights
Watch have warned
that the continued use of the
powers erodes

41:54.345 --> 41:59.083 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the rule of law and undermines
the rights
of citizens.

41:59.117 --> 42:04.689 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Eiffel Tower and other
landmarks may radiate
an abiding allure, but terrorism
has cast

42:04.722 --> 42:07.692 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
a permanent shadow on the City
of Light.

42:07.725 --> 42:12.830 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's no longer possible to take
a leisurely
stroll beneath the steel
latticework without

42:12.864 --> 42:15.700 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
first undergoing security
screening.

42:15.733 --> 42:21.205 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The impression that this is a
country on a
war footing with an invisible
enemy is reinforced

42:21.239 --> 42:23.207 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
by military patrols.

42:23.241 --> 42:28.713 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Colombe Brossel, the deputy
mayor, with responsibility
for security issues, says the
authorities

42:28.746 --> 42:30.515 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
are trying to strike a balance.

42:30.548 --> 42:33.184 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
COLOMBE BROSSEL, Deputy Mayor of
Paris (through
translator): Our wish, our
directive line,

42:33.217 --> 42:37.855 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
is to say, we have to give our
best, our maximum
when it comes to security
questions.

42:37.889 --> 42:42.293 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, of course, the way we
organize the events
is different compared to 18
months ago, two

42:42.326 --> 42:44.095 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
or five years ago.

42:44.128 --> 42:48.099 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But we remain adamant on the
fact that Paris
needs to remain a city where
anyone can go

42:48.132 --> 42:51.969 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
out, where we can have events in
the public
space, where we can share
moments of pleasure

42:52.003 --> 42:53.771 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
and happiness.

42:53.805 --> 42:56.574 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRANCOIS GERE, President, French
Strategic
Analysis Institute: The Islamic
State is losing

42:56.607 --> 43:00.845 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ground, is losing also prestige
and glory.

43:00.878 --> 43:05.783 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: Historian
Francois Gere,
president of the French
Strategic Analysis

43:05.817 --> 43:11.222 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Institute, believes that France
will almost
certainly be hit again by
Islamic State, although

43:11.255 --> 43:14.392 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
he's convinced the
organization's potency
is diminishing.

43:14.425 --> 43:21.666 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRANCOIS GERE: It's obvious that
the Islamic
State will try to send
additional people in

43:21.699 --> 43:27.505 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
order to perpetrate attacks and
terrorist
aggressions in Europe.

43:27.538 --> 43:33.611 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There is still a period of high
danger during
the coming six months.

43:33.644 --> 43:35.680 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
After that, it will decrease.

43:35.713 --> 43:40.184 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: The Marais is
one district
that's especially vigilant, not
least because

43:40.218 --> 43:43.588 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of the high concentration of
Jewish businesses
and institutions.

43:43.621 --> 43:47.458 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MAN (through translator): We're
scared, but
we have to keep living normally.

43:47.492 --> 43:51.229 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAN (through translator): At
every synagogue
and school, you have dozens of
soldiers.

43:51.262 --> 43:54.332 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I'm relaxed about it because
it's easier for
us Jews to wear the kippa.

43:54.365 --> 44:00.838 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WOMAN: During this whole year, I
think the
thing was to say to yourself,
keep on living.

44:00.872 --> 44:06.644 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You cannot live in fear, and you
just need
to carry on your daily life as
normal.

44:06.677 --> 44:10.314 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Otherwise, yes, where do we go?

44:10.348 --> 44:15.486 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: Stephane
Balensi is considering
selling his clothes shop.

44:15.520 --> 44:18.856 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Sales have plunged by 40 percent
over the
past year.

44:18.890 --> 44:23.494 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Although he's reassured by
military patrols,
he believes they frighten
tourists away.

44:23.528 --> 44:27.698 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
STEPHANE BALENSI, Business Owner
(through
translator): It started with the
13th of November.

44:27.732 --> 44:32.236 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Quite clearly, ever since the
Bataclan and
then during the normally busy
summer season,

44:32.270 --> 44:33.638 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
we had the Nice attacks.

44:33.671 --> 44:35.840 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It's the same, far less tourism.

44:35.873 --> 44:41.012 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: Beligh Nabli is
a political
scientist and analyst of the
Islamic world.

44:41.045 --> 44:45.917 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He says intolerance towards
Muslims has become
more overt since the attacks.

44:45.950 --> 44:49.287 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
BELIGH NABLI, Political
Scientist (through
translator): A lot of people
kept their Islamophobia

44:49.320 --> 44:53.524 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
hidden before, but now they feel
it's OK to
express their aversion and
criticism of Islam

44:53.558 --> 44:56.294 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
in general and towards Muslims
in particular.

44:56.327 --> 45:00.264 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's created a new social
tension, which has
given more justification to the
jihadis in

45:00.298 --> 45:04.902 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
their strategy of dividing
French society
in order to lure back the Muslim
community

45:04.936 --> 45:06.704 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to their cause.

45:06.737 --> 45:10.708 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: France is
gearing up for
a presidential election in six
months' time.

45:10.741 --> 45:15.413 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The latest opinion polls suggest
that almost
a third of the electorate
believe the hard-line

45:15.446 --> 45:20.985 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
stance of Marine Le Pen, leader
of the right-wing
National Front, would make the
country a safer

45:21.018 --> 45:22.753 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
place.

45:22.787 --> 45:29.660 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But the divisions in society
exposed by last
year's attacks worry those most
affected.

45:29.694 --> 45:35.733 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GEORGES SALINES: Candidates are
playing this
card, and it's a very dangerous
path, because

45:35.766 --> 45:46.577 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the most important thing is to
be precise
in targeting the terrorists, the
extremists,

45:46.611 --> 45:54.418 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Da'esh, and not doing anything
which could
help them to recruit.

45:54.452 --> 45:59.123 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CAROLINE LANGLADE (through
translator): I
think that the most beautiful
response we

45:59.156 --> 46:03.527 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
can give the terrorists is love,
joy, happiness,
culture, music.

46:03.561 --> 46:06.464 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, we need to keep this going
as loud as
possible.

46:06.497 --> 46:13.337 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, yes, I hope we will continue
even stronger,
that people will realize that
life isn't about

46:13.371 --> 46:14.639 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the money.

46:14.672 --> 46:17.942 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Life doesn't revolve around the
little problems
we might have.

46:17.975 --> 46:21.579 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Life is love.

46:21.612 --> 46:29.086 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: But while Paris
puts on a
brave face, a new survey shows
that terrorism

46:29.120 --> 46:33.891 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
remains the biggest concern of
almost half
the French population.

46:33.924 --> 46:38.863 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They fear that Islamic State
will follow through
on a threat made earlier this
year to intensify

46:38.896 --> 46:43.601 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
attacks on France in revenge for
its military
role against the caliphate, a
world away from

46:43.634 --> 46:44.802 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Notre Dame.

